cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with pose estimation using deep learning methods, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new loss function and optimization method, which falls under the category of machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. The problem of pose estimation also has applications in robotics and control, which fall under the categories of cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.GR (Graphics), respectively. Finally, the paper uses a dataset to calculate hyper-parameters, which is a common practice in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well.
